  <description>Leaves crisped and curled when dry, plane in many leaves, 2-stratose in distal 1/2, cells with longitudinal striolae in distal 1/2 of leaf; usually a few alar cells enlarged on margins, often colored.  Specialized asexual reproduction absent.  Capsule without differentiated annulus; peristome vertically striolate basally, weakly papillose distally.</description>
  <phenology>Capsules mature spring–early summer.</phenology>
  <habitat>Forming cushions on siliceous rock or gravel, occasionally epiphytic or epixylic;</habitat>
  <elevation>10–2000 m;</elevation>
